---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Cluless Context-Aware Digital Closet | Aryan">
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-container px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-white/50">Project</p>
        <h1 class="mt-4 font-heading text-4xl">Cluless Context-Aware Digital Closet</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-white/60">
         
        </p>
        <div class="article-content mt-10">
          <p></p>
          <p>Turning wardrobes into intelligent outfit recommendations.</p>
          <p>
            Cluless is a mobile-first web application that helps users decide what to wear by digitizing their wardrobe
            and generating outfit suggestions based on context such as weather, occasion, and personal style
            preferences.
          </p>
          <p>
            The idea came from a simple but common problem: many people own large wardrobes yet still struggle with
            daily outfit decisions. Most fashion platforms focus on inspiration (Pinterest, Instagram), but they rarely
            translate those ideas into practical suggestions using clothes people already own.
          </p>
          <p>
            Cluless addresses this gap by combining wardrobe management with a lightweight recommendation system that
            generates outfit suggestions tailored to the user's actual clothing items.
          </p>

          <h2>Problem</h2>
          <p>
            People often experience decision fatigue when choosing what to wear. Even with many clothing options,
            selecting an outfit that fits the weather, occasion, and personal style can take unnecessary time.
          </p>
          <p>Existing solutions have limitations:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Inspiration platforms provide ideas but don't consider a user's wardrobe.</li>
            <li>Closet management apps track inventory but rarely provide intelligent recommendations.</li>
            <li>Weather apps provide environmental context but don't translate it into clothing decisions.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            There is an opportunity to create a system that connects these elements into a single decision-support
            tool.
          </p>

          <h2>Solution</h2>
          <p>
            Cluless digitizes a user's wardrobe and generates outfit combinations that fit their context.
          </p>
          <p>Users can:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Upload clothing items into a digital closet.</li>
            <li>Receive outfit suggestions based on weather conditions.</li>
            <li>Provide feedback on recommendations so the system improves over time.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            The goal is to move from simple wardrobe storage to a context-aware personal style assistant.
          </p>

          <h2>Key Features</h2>
          <p>Digital Closet</p>
          <p>
            Users upload and manage clothing items through a simple mobile interface. Each item is categorized and
            stored as part of the user's personal wardrobe inventory.
          </p>
          <p>Weather-Aware Outfit Suggestions</p>
          <p>
            The system integrates weather data and filters wardrobe items based on warmth and formality attributes to
            generate appropriate outfit combinations.
          </p>
          <p>Feedback-Based Learning</p>
          <p>
            Users can provide feedback on generated outfits (like, dislike, too hot, too formal). This feedback is used
            to adjust future recommendations.
          </p>
          <p>Mobile-First Design</p>
          <p>
            The application is built as a Progressive Web App designed for quick daily use, optimized for mobile
            devices.
          </p>

          <h2>Product Thinking</h2>
          <p>
            Cluless focuses on actionable recommendations rather than passive inspiration. Instead of showing endless
            outfit images, the system works with the user's existing wardrobe to generate combinations that are
            immediately usable.
          </p>
          <p>The product follows a simple loop:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Digitize wardrobe</li>
            <li>Generate outfit suggestions</li>
            <li>Collect feedback</li>
            <li>Improve recommendations</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            This feedback loop allows the system to gradually learn a user's style preferences.
          </p>

          <h2>Technology</h2>
          <p>Frontend:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Next.js (Progressive Web App)</li>
            <li>TypeScript</li>
            <li>Tailwind CSS</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Backend:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Supabase (authentication, database, and storage)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>External APIs:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Weather API for contextual recommendations.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            The architecture prioritizes fast iteration and a lightweight infrastructure suitable for early-stage
            product development.
          </p>

          <h2>Future Direction</h2>
          <p>Future iterations of Cluless could expand beyond basic outfit generation to include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>wardrobe analytics</li>
            <li>trend-to-closet mapping</li>
            <li>packing assistants for travel</li>
            <li>style preference modeling</li>
            <li>wardrobe gap detection</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            The long-term vision is to build a personal style intelligence system that helps users better understand
            and utilize their wardrobes.
          </p>

          <h2>Status</h2>
          <p>
            Currently in active development as an MVP, with a focus on validating user engagement and improving
            recommendation quality through user feedback.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
